<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-432-618  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 432 618.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 11 1990 n1423* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Up to 30,000 jobs expected to go at British Telecom. (BritishTelecommunications Plc)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (management).andO;Topic:     ReorganizationLayoffStockManagementTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UP TO 30,000 JOBS EXPECTED TO GO AT BRITISH TELECOMandM;British Telecommunications Plc yesterday fleshed out its plans to reorganiseits 27 districts, each under its own management, into just three divisions -Business Communications, Personal Communications and Worldwide Networks.andO;Cuts are heavier than feared, with between 4,000 and 5,000 managers to losetheir jobs over the next 12 months, and up to 30,000 people to be shed in thenext two or three years - a cut representing 10% of the staff.andP;  The Citywasn't overly impressed and the shares fell 4p to 248.5p.andO;</TEXT></DOC>